Geoffrey George Farnfield (13 July 1897 – 22 March 1974) was an English cricketer.  Farnfield was a right-handed batsman.  He was born at West Ham, Essex.
Farnfield played 12 first-class matches for Essex in the 1921 County Championship, making his debut against Surrey, with his final game coming against Kent.  In his 12 first-class matches, he scored 252 runs at a batting average of 13.26, with a high score of 41.He died at Leamington Spa, Warwickshire on 22 March 1974.
